Revert 0115's KeyGen->CC dispatch encoding back to the HW-proven CCBS model

Board patch 0115 ("sdk-convergent-bringup") changed the KeyGen scheme CC
next-engine dispatch from the HW-proven CCBS model (0106) -

    KGSE_MODE NIA = ENQUEUE_KG_DFLT_NIA (BMI direct-enqueue, 0x80500002)
    KGSE_CCBS    = MURAM offset of the CC root group table  (non-zero)

- to the AC_CC NIA-flip model -

    KGSE_MODE NIA = NIA_ENG_FM_CTL | NIA_FM_CTL_AC_CC       (0x80000006)
    KGSE_CCBS    = 0

on the theory that the earlier CCBS "stall" was caused by a missing FMBM_RCCB
bind + non-SDK root AD rather than the encoding. That theory was DISPROVEN on
hardware (iter-48, 2026-06-12, DUT 192.168.1.190): with 0115's RCCB bind +
0116's SDK result-AD + 0117's 210.10.1 ucode all in place, the AC_CC encoding
still stalls the FMan port (FMFP_PS[STL]) on the first CC-dispatched frame,
whereas live-rewriting the grafted scheme back to CCBS (mode 0x80000006 ->
0x80500002, ccbs 0 -> live FMBM_RCCB value 0x0005ac00) cured the stall
completely (no STL in 60s, frames flowed, ping 5/5 0% loss).

This patch reverts ONLY 0115's three KeyGen/CC-scheme files
(fman_keygen.c, fman_keygen_internal.h, fman_pcd_kg.c) back to the CCBS
encoding. It deliberately KEEPS the rest of 0115 - the FMBM_RCCB bind in
dpaa_fman_caps.c (fman_port_set_cc_base), the SDK-format result AD in
fman_pcd_cc.c, and the fman_port.c lookup helper - as well as all of 0116
(FM_CTL pre-BMI enqueue AD + ctrl-params page) and 0117 (FMan controller
microcode loader). The net effect makes the mainline driver dispatch CC the
way the NXP SDK does: NIA stays BMI direct-enqueue and the non-zero KGSE_CCBS
(root group-table MURAM offset, bound per-port via FMBM_RCCB) drives the
implicit CC walk.

Co-authored-by: Copilot <223556219+Copilot@users.noreply.github.com>

